    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i've tried that, but the log data is getting massive because of how frequently the allocators are being called, and it's making the serial buffer overflow. i'm basically looking for a needle in a haystack. \n\nis there a way to use some kind of statistical approach or \"canary\" method? like, instead of logging everything, can i implement something that only triggers when an allocation looks suspicious or deviates from the expected lifecycle? i need a way to catch these elusive little leaks without drowning in data.",
