    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Implement a probabilistic sampling or \"canary\" logging approach on your allocator. Instead of logging every allocation, assign a small, random probability (e.g., 1 in 1000) to trigger an allocation trace log, which dramatically reduces log spam while still capturing occasional misbehaving allocations. Alternatively, track the *rate* of allocation/deallocation for critical object types; if the allocation rate persistently exceeds the deallocation rate over a short window, flag that object type for intensified, short-burst logging.",
      "source": "target",
